t\":\"**Inspecting Java dependencies**\\n\\nI'm looking into whether version 2.3 has a Java 1.3 classfile, and it seems like it works with Java 25. I’m leaning towards recommending the javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.3, but I’d need to check artifact classfile references. I don't think I need the Maven dependency tree, and it looks like no Docker image is necessary for the WebDAV server; testing can be done in-memory. Also, I should check built-in tests for basic coverage without needing an external server.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5nG0Xn4hE4lrMnXZCwK9TCld|fc_0ea829d8f98b67a8016a42a2fef2bc81958bc33fcff6432477", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, zipfile, io\nurl='https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/jackrabbit/jackrabbit-webdav/2.0-beta4/jackrabbit-webdav-2.0-beta4-test-sources.jar'\ntry:\n data=urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=30).read()\n z=zipfile.ZipFile(io.BytesIO(data))\n print('entries', len(z.namelist()))\n for name in z.namelist()[:50]: print(name)\n serv=0\n for name in z.namelist():\n  if name.endswith('.java'):\n   txt=z.read(name).decode(errors='replace')\n   if 'javax.servlet' in txt or 'AbstractWebdavServlet' in txt:\n    print('serv/test',name)\n    serv+=1\n print('serv tests',serv)\nexcept Exception as e: print('ERR',e)\nPY", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 22672, "output": 612, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 23284, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782751990575, "responseId": "resp_0ea829d8f98b67a8016a42a2f70cf88195a835f66be8c38fd6"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_5nG0Xn4hE4lrMnXZCwK9TCld|fc_0ea829d8f98b67a8016a42a2fef2bc81958bc33fcff6432477", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ERR HTTP Error 404: Not Found\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 17827520000